Description: Wooden shabti of Sety I with a lappet-wig, a modelled face and parallel hands; six rows of Hieroglyphic text on the leg section; traces of bitumen.
Exhibition history: 2017-2018 10 Oct-14 April, Sir John Soane’s Museum, London, The Great Belzoni: Egyptology’s Pioneer
Acquisition name: Donated by: Lt-Gen Augustus W H Meyrick
